This is an out-of-tree STM32MP257 TSN DKMS module package for Debian 13 arm64.

The package configures DKMS immediately. Matching headers for the running kernel
are mandatory:

  apt install linux-headers-$(uname -r) build-essential dkms

A failed DKMS build is intentionally fatal and leaves the compiler log at:

  /var/lib/dkms/@MODULE_NAME@/@DKMS_VERSION@/build/make.log

The failed registration is removed before the package reports the failure. During
removal or upgrade, DKMS is removed from the package prerm script while this
package's /usr/src tree still exists. This prevents a broken DKMS symlink from
blocking a later apt purge.
